The chief points of difference between the “Menaechmi ”. and “The Comedy of Errors ’⁹ are, that the part of Peniculus is entirely wanting in the latter, and that the part of Erotium in the “ Menaechmi ” is made much more prominent than that of the corresponding char- acter in Shakspeare's play. Shakspeare more than compensates for the loss of these two characters by the introduction of the two Bromios, who as servants of the two leadingcharacters carry still further the complication of the plot arising from mistaken identity.
